				\begin{document}$${\lambda }_{{\rm{cont}}}=2$$\end{document}λcont=2), the energy cost for the advancement of the leading cells is low, resulting in a smooth migration of the monolayer; see Fig. 8(a). However, when with the cortex contractility is strong (e.g., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
